by Role: Permissions at higher levels are Field Level permissions. All Fields have a Permission Level set against them and the rules defined at that permissions apply to the field. This is useful in case you want to hide or make certain field read-only for certain Roles.

by Role: Permissions at level 0 are Document Level permissions, i.e. they are primary for access to the document.
